1
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:12,633
<i> No!</i>

2
00:00:12,767 --> 00:00:14,000
<i> Did Emma tell you to do this?</i>

3
00:00:14,133 --> 00:00:15,200
<i> Stop!</i>

4
00:00:15,333 --> 00:00:16,700
<i> Did you see a woman?</i>

5
00:00:16,833 --> 00:00:18,600
<i>She's wearing white
and this tall.</i>

6
00:00:18,733 --> 00:00:19,233
<i> I didn't.</i>

7
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:20,300
<i> Bro, bro.</i>

8
00:00:20,433 --> 00:00:21,833
<i>I think I saw who
you're looking for.</i>

9
00:00:21,967 --> 00:00:22,867
<i> She went over there.</i>

10
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:24,567
<i> I ran into her earlier.</i>

11
00:00:24,700 --> 00:00:25,233
<i> Are you sure?</i>

12
00:00:25,367 --> 00:00:25,867
<i> Yes, I am.</i>

13
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:26,567
<i> What are you doing?</i>

14
00:00:27,700 --> 00:00:28,900
<i> She pushed me!</i>

15
00:00:29,033 --> 00:00:31,000
<i>I'm sorry,
but I didn't push her.</i>

16
00:00:31,133 --> 00:00:32,533
<i> Someone's chasing me.</i>

17
00:00:32,667 --> 00:00:33,300
<i> Mom!</i>

18
00:00:33,433 --> 00:00:34,233
<i> Ma'am, where are you going?</i>

19
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:36,300
<i>That woman reminded me
of my mom.</i>

20
00:00:36,433 --> 00:00:37,533
<i> Mookie is my girlfriend.</i>

21
00:00:37,667 --> 00:00:41,700
<i>I hope you get someone
presentable and with grace.</i>

22
00:00:41,833 --> 00:00:42,800
<i> I'll go ahead.</i>

23
00:00:42,933 --> 00:00:44,667
<i>I'll introduce you again
to my mom.</i>

24
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:46,100
<i> The girl I fell in love with.</i>

25
00:00:46,233 --> 00:00:47,733
<i> You and me, okay?</i>

26
00:00:47,867 --> 00:00:51,033
<i>I want to see that she can
no longer rise from that grave!</i>

27
00:00:51,167 --> 00:00:52,800
<i>We really can't do anything.
We can't dig deeper anymore.</i>

28
00:00:52,933 --> 00:00:54,633
<i> No!</i>

29
00:01:32,733 --> 00:01:34,633
I need to beat Emma.

30
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:38,167
But how?

31
00:01:38,300 --> 00:01:38,900
How?

32
00:01:41,700 --> 00:01:43,967
How can I know where she's
hiding?

33
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:45,800
I know what to do.

34
00:01:47,533 --> 00:01:48,467
Altair!

35
00:01:49,633 --> 00:01:52,267
We need to get to Altair!

36
00:01:52,400 --> 00:01:57,167
So, find that double-crossing
private investigator.

37
00:01:57,300 --> 00:01:58,400
Now!

38
00:02:03,133 --> 00:02:05,467
<i> Did you miss me, Sis?</i>

39
00:02:05,600 --> 00:02:06,800
No!

40
00:02:06,933 --> 00:02:08,333
No!

41
00:02:08,467 --> 00:02:11,033
<i>Can't you accept that I tricked
you?</i>

42
00:02:11,167 --> 00:02:12,400
You're not here.

43
00:02:12,533 --> 00:02:15,133
<i>Who's the dumb one between us
now, Jade?</i>

44
00:02:15,300 --> 00:02:24,433
No!

45
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:43,867
- Miss, can I sit here?
- Sure, Ma'am.

46
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,000
Thank you.

47
00:02:57,733 --> 00:03:01,567
<i>Lord, thank you for letting me
escape from Olive.</i>

48
00:03:01,700 --> 00:03:03,767
<i>But is there a need for a
replacement?</i>

49
00:03:03,900 --> 00:03:05,967
<i> Why did Ador suddenly show up?</i>

50
00:03:13,967 --> 00:03:14,500
Miss.

51
00:03:16,167 --> 00:03:17,267
One order.

52
00:03:18,333 --> 00:03:19,933
Please give it to her.

53
00:03:20,067 --> 00:03:21,000
Okay.

54
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:42,300
Help!

55
00:03:42,433 --> 00:03:43,700
Who are you?

56
00:03:43,833 --> 00:03:45,267
Where am I?

57
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:46,700
Help!

58
00:03:46,833 --> 00:03:49,233
Help!

59
00:03:49,367 --> 00:03:51,767
Where am I? Who are you?

60
00:03:51,900 --> 00:03:53,500
What are you going to do to me?

61
00:03:56,567 --> 00:03:57,300
Where am I?

62
00:03:58,533 --> 00:03:59,700
Help!

63
00:04:01,100 --> 00:04:02,333
Please help me!

64
00:04:08,100 --> 00:04:10,167
You traitor.

65
00:04:10,300 --> 00:04:11,733
What do you need from me?

66
00:04:12,933 --> 00:04:13,967
Emma.

67
00:04:15,633 --> 00:04:17,733
Where's Emma?

68
00:04:17,867 --> 00:04:19,367
Didn't I kill her?

69
00:04:23,433 --> 00:04:25,500
You killed her?

70
00:04:27,133 --> 00:04:33,100
But her body isn't
in the grave.

71
00:04:34,967 --> 00:04:38,700
So, I'll give you another
chance, Altair.

72
00:04:40,933 --> 00:04:42,167
Where's Emma?

73
00:04:43,633 --> 00:04:45,033
I don't know.

74
00:04:45,167 --> 00:04:46,433
I don't know.

75
00:04:57,167 --> 00:04:59,667
Are you sure about your answer?

76
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:00,733
Miss Jade.

77
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:04,233
I will give you another
chance

78
00:05:04,367 --> 00:05:05,867
to provide me with a proper
answer.

79
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:08,067
Miss Jade,
I'm telling you the truth.

80
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:09,700
I really don't know.

81
00:05:09,833 --> 00:05:12,133
I don't want to get involved
in your fight.

82
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:15,933
Miss Jade.

83
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:19,267
Wrong answer.

84
00:05:20,367 --> 00:05:21,867
Miss Jade,
I'm telling the truth.

85
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:25,067
I want to change my ways
for my family.

86
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:30,700
I can help you if you want
to live a new life.

87
00:05:30,833 --> 00:05:33,467
But that depends
on your answer.

88
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:38,633
So again, I'll ask you.

89
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:42,000
Where's Emma?

90
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:43,800
No matter how you ask me,

91
00:05:43,933 --> 00:05:46,900
I can't say anything
because I don't know!

92
00:05:47,033 --> 00:05:50,767
<i> Liar. He'll fool you again.</i>

93
00:05:50,900 --> 00:05:52,533
We can't trust him.

94
00:05:52,667 --> 00:05:55,767
<i>Will you let him fool you again?</i>

95
00:05:55,900 --> 00:05:57,000
No.

96
00:05:57,133 --> 00:05:58,567
No way.

97
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:09,800
Miss, I did not order that. I'll
only sit here for a while.

98
00:06:09,967 --> 00:06:12,200
Someone ordered for you, Ma'am.

99
00:06:12,333 --> 00:06:13,567
Who did?

100
00:06:37,467 --> 00:06:38,500
- Hey...
- Ligaya.

101
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:41,633
Don't touch me.

102
00:06:42,733 --> 00:06:45,900
I'll make a scene if you do.
Don't touch me.

103
00:06:56,467 --> 00:06:57,833
That's too bad.

104
00:06:57,967 --> 00:07:00,700
Miss Jade!

105
00:07:03,300 --> 00:07:05,267
Miss Jade,
have mercy on my family!

106
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:06,967
I really don't know anything!

107
00:07:08,100 --> 00:07:09,733
Miss Jade!

108
00:07:09,867 --> 00:07:11,100
Miss Jade!

109
00:07:11,233 --> 00:07:13,900
Miss Jade, I'm begging you.
I have a family!

110
00:07:14,033 --> 00:07:15,600
What's that?

111
00:07:15,767 --> 00:07:16,900
Miss Jade, what's that?

112
00:07:19,100 --> 00:07:19,833
What's that?

113
00:07:21,733 --> 00:07:22,600
What's that?

114
00:07:25,100 --> 00:07:26,467
Miss Jade!

115
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:27,633
Miss Jade, don't!

116
00:07:27,767 --> 00:07:28,400
Don't!

117
00:07:28,533 --> 00:07:29,633
Don't!

118
00:07:35,567 --> 00:07:36,700
What's that?

119
00:07:52,267 --> 00:07:53,933
I'm begging you.

120
00:07:54,067 --> 00:07:55,633
Please.

121
00:07:55,767 --> 00:07:58,633
Let me go, Ador.

122
00:07:58,767 --> 00:08:00,633
Let me be.

123
00:08:00,767 --> 00:08:02,500
Ligaya.

124
00:08:02,633 --> 00:08:04,467
Ligaya, I won't hurt you.

125
00:08:06,833 --> 00:08:09,100
I won't do anything to harm you.

126
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:16,467
What do you need?

127
00:08:18,067 --> 00:08:19,833
Please forgive me, Ligaya.

128
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:23,933
What do you need from me?

129
00:08:25,567 --> 00:08:26,467
Nothing.

130
00:08:27,633 --> 00:08:30,533
I only want to make sure
you're safe.

131
00:08:32,233 --> 00:08:36,567
And those who are chasing you
won't be able to follow you.

132
00:08:36,700 --> 00:08:37,833
That's all.

133
00:08:39,100 --> 00:08:40,400
How did you know...

134
00:08:44,167 --> 00:08:46,167
<i>Bro, I think I saw who you're
looking for.</i>

135
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:47,100
<i> Really?</i>

136
00:08:47,233 --> 00:08:47,967
<i> Yes.</i>

137
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:53,200
<i>She went that way.
I ran into her earlier.</i>

138
00:08:53,333 --> 00:08:56,033
<i>- Okay. Thank you.
- You're welcome.</i>

139
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:00,533
Was that you?

140
00:09:00,667 --> 00:09:06,967
I couldn't show up to you
because I feel ashamed.

141
00:09:08,067 --> 00:09:09,633
I have no face to show you...

142
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:14,667
after everything I did before.

143
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:24,700
- Ligaya, please forgive me.
- Don't come near me.

144
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:31,067
So that's why I dream of you.

145
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:33,700
We'll still see each other,
you monster.

146
00:09:35,900 --> 00:09:39,267
Don't touch me.
I said don't touch me.

147
00:09:40,667 --> 00:09:42,233
I'm sorry, Ligaya.

148
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:46,767
I made your life a hell.

149
00:09:48,533 --> 00:09:49,700
I regretted it.

150
00:09:51,867 --> 00:09:53,167
But it was all in vain.

151
00:09:55,233 --> 00:09:56,600
You gave up on me.

152
00:09:56,733 --> 00:10:00,667
Any woman would give up on you.

153
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:03,767
Because you're not only
a bad father.

154
00:10:03,933 --> 00:10:06,967
You're not only a bad husband.

155
00:10:07,100 --> 00:10:10,233
You really are a bad person.

156
00:10:10,367 --> 00:10:18,400
You're the worst. You animal!
Demon!

157
00:10:18,533 --> 00:10:21,633
My life was ruined
because of you!

158
00:10:21,767 --> 00:10:26,667
My children's lives were ruined
because of you.

159
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:35,900
Animal!

160
00:10:36,067 --> 00:10:37,933
Please forgive me, Ligaya.

161
00:10:40,300 --> 00:10:43,133
I'm done with this.

162
00:11:06,700 --> 00:11:10,167
Olive, did you just kill him?

163
00:11:10,333 --> 00:11:11,467
Oh yeah, I did.

164
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:14,200
It's his fault.

165
00:11:16,333 --> 00:11:18,467
They're all the same.

166
00:11:21,067 --> 00:11:23,267
They choose someone else
over me.

167
00:11:25,900 --> 00:11:31,667
They choose Emma if not Jade.

168
00:11:33,900 --> 00:11:35,400
Emma might be hearing us.

169
00:11:37,067 --> 00:11:39,200
She might be watching me now.

170
00:11:41,733 --> 00:11:44,433
Maybe she knows my plans.

171
00:11:46,767 --> 00:11:48,633
That's why I need to get to her.

172
00:11:50,167 --> 00:11:52,100
I need to beat her to it.

173
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:56,800
I need to get her
out of her lair.

174
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:03,667
And I think I know
just how to do that.

175
00:12:12,367 --> 00:12:14,300
Why don't you seem happy?

176
00:12:14,467 --> 00:12:16,100
You succeeded again.

177
00:12:16,233 --> 00:12:20,500
It's so fun to watch Jade
tipping over.

178
00:12:20,633 --> 00:12:22,500
I'm happy, Flor.

179
00:12:22,633 --> 00:12:27,733
And it feels good to see
Jade becoming unsettled.

180
00:12:27,867 --> 00:12:29,600
But...

181
00:12:29,733 --> 00:12:34,967
I can't be truly happy
when Mom isn't around.

182
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:38,767
I saw an old lady earlier.
I thought it was her.

183
00:12:38,900 --> 00:12:40,900
I think I focused too much
on Jade.

184
00:12:41,033 --> 00:12:43,133
I forgot about Mom.

185
00:12:43,267 --> 00:12:44,400
Come on.

186
00:12:46,867 --> 00:12:49,067
Miss Ligaya will understand.

187
00:12:49,233 --> 00:12:51,667
And if she's here,

188
00:12:51,800 --> 00:12:55,100
I'm sure she'll tell you
to keep getting Mookie back.

189
00:12:55,233 --> 00:12:56,400
Just go.

190
00:12:56,533 --> 00:12:59,367
That's exactly what Mom will do.

191
00:12:59,500 --> 00:13:03,433
Once I get my daughter,
we'll find my mom together.

192
00:13:03,567 --> 00:13:06,167
There you go.
Use that as your motivation.

193
00:13:06,300 --> 00:13:08,333
Your longing for Miss Ligaya.

194
00:13:08,467 --> 00:13:13,000
So that you'll defeat the first
lady of darkness real fast.

195
00:13:13,133 --> 00:13:14,833
Always, Flor.

196
00:13:14,967 --> 00:13:17,700
She and Mookie
are my inspiration.

197
00:13:17,833 --> 00:13:21,233
I want us to be together again.

198
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:22,867
Right?

199
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:24,000
Flor?

200
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:27,133
Ma'am.

201
00:13:29,300 --> 00:13:30,967
I'm going home.

202
00:13:31,100 --> 00:13:32,800
I need something from you.

203
00:13:32,933 --> 00:13:34,133
What is it, Ma'am?

204
00:13:34,267 --> 00:13:35,067
It's Emma.

205
00:13:45,233 --> 00:13:47,367
- Emma?
- You know where she is, right?

206
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:49,100
Ma'am, no.

207
00:13:49,233 --> 00:13:50,700
It's been a while since
we last saw each other.

208
00:13:50,833 --> 00:13:53,400
Come on, Flor.

209
00:13:53,533 --> 00:13:54,267
Ma'am...

210
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:56,233
I know you know where Emma is.

211
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:57,800
Ma'am, what are you talking
about?

212
00:13:57,933 --> 00:13:59,967
- I don't know, Ma'am.
- So, tell me.

213
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:01,733
Where's Emma?

214
00:14:01,867 --> 00:14:04,267
I really don't know, Ma'am.

215
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:07,267
Don't cover for her.

216
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:08,300
Ma'am.

217
00:14:08,433 --> 00:14:10,267
I know you know where Emma is.

218
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:12,233
I really don't know, Ma'am.

219
00:14:13,533 --> 00:14:14,967
<i> Don't believe her.</i>

220
00:14:15,100 --> 00:14:16,333
<i> She's a liar.</i>

221
00:14:16,467 --> 00:14:19,133
<i>Liar.
Don't believe her.</i>

222
00:14:20,167 --> 00:14:21,933
Oh, please. Stop lying.

223
00:14:22,067 --> 00:14:23,067
Ma'am.

224
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:26,200
I let you work here
because I want to trust you.

225
00:14:26,333 --> 00:14:28,533
So, are you really trustworthy?

226
00:14:28,700 --> 00:14:30,033
Ma'am, promise...

227
00:14:30,167 --> 00:14:31,467
Where's Emma?

228
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:33,167
- I really don't know...
- Won't you confess?

229
00:14:33,300 --> 00:14:34,300
Ma'am, I really don't know.

230
00:14:34,433 --> 00:14:35,367
Ma'am, I'm getting hurt.

231
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:37,633
Ma'am, please stop.

232
00:14:37,767 --> 00:14:41,000
- Tell me where Emma is.
- Ma'am, I don't know anything.

233
00:14:41,133 --> 00:14:42,167
Ma'am, please stop.

234
00:14:42,300 --> 00:14:43,233
Auntie Jade!

235
00:14:43,367 --> 00:14:44,300
Auntie Jade!

236
00:14:44,433 --> 00:14:46,500
Mookie!

237
00:14:46,633 --> 00:14:47,700
Mookie, please help me.

238
00:14:47,833 --> 00:14:48,800
She's scary.

239
00:14:48,933 --> 00:14:51,233
She's insisting that I know
where your mom is.

240
00:14:51,367 --> 00:14:53,167
Auntie Jade, what's happening?

241
00:14:54,433 --> 00:14:55,500
Quiet!

242
00:14:55,633 --> 00:14:56,733
Emma's here!

243
00:14:58,067 --> 00:14:59,400
She hears us.

244
00:14:59,533 --> 00:15:00,100
Auntie Jade!

245
00:15:00,233 --> 00:15:00,900
- She's here
- Mookie!

246
00:15:01,033 --> 00:15:01,833
- Mookie!
- Emma!

247
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:02,933
Don't follow her.

248
00:15:03,067 --> 00:15:05,133
- It's dangerous.
- Emma, I can hear you.

249
00:15:05,267 --> 00:15:06,400
She seems to be losing her mind.

250
00:15:06,533 --> 00:15:08,267
She's like Ma'am Olive.

251
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:09,867
So, don't. Stay here, okay?

252
00:15:11,267 --> 00:15:13,600
But what'shappening to her?

253
00:15:13,733 --> 00:15:15,700
I can't understand her anymore.

254
00:15:15,833 --> 00:15:17,067
I don't know.

255
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:18,767
I'm getting scared too.

256
00:15:19,833 --> 00:15:21,833
I wonder why she's behaving
like that.

257
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:41,400
Come in, come in.

258
00:15:41,533 --> 00:15:43,033
I'm sorry for the mess.

259
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:10,367
That's a lot of locks.

260
00:16:13,367 --> 00:16:17,800
A lot of people want to steal my
spot.

261
00:16:18,833 --> 00:16:19,867
Sit down first.

262
00:16:28,100 --> 00:16:29,200
I'm sorry.

263
00:16:33,700 --> 00:16:34,467
Here.

264
00:16:36,833 --> 00:16:40,400
It looks dirty,
but I just washed it.

265
00:16:42,533 --> 00:16:43,767
Thank you.

266
00:16:50,900 --> 00:16:52,767
Did our daughter do that?

267
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:57,100
She's taking revenge against me.

268
00:16:59,167 --> 00:17:02,233
She blames me for her ruined
life.

269
00:17:11,667 --> 00:17:13,567
She should blame me instead.

270
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:14,800
Yes.

271
00:17:19,233 --> 00:17:21,033
Because if you had become
a good husband...

272
00:17:22,967 --> 00:17:25,100
if you had become a responsible
father...

273
00:17:26,667 --> 00:17:29,100
I would have a nice family now.

274
00:17:33,033 --> 00:17:37,067
I only went with you
because I need help.

275
00:17:40,767 --> 00:17:43,167
I will do everything for you,
Ligaya.

276
00:17:44,633 --> 00:17:46,033
Even if I know...

277
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:52,667
I can feel that you don't fully
trust me.

278
00:17:56,633 --> 00:17:58,367
I understand.

279
00:18:00,100 --> 00:18:02,567
I've done a very bad thing to
you.

280
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:11,900
I'll find us something to eat.

281
00:18:12,033 --> 00:18:13,600
Go and get changed.

282
00:18:50,267 --> 00:18:51,033
Jade?

283
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:56,333
What are you doing?

284
00:18:58,567 --> 00:18:59,500
Why do you look like that?

285
00:18:59,633 --> 00:19:00,467
Hey, Jade!

286
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:01,833
Do you even sleep?

287
00:19:01,967 --> 00:19:03,033
Quiet!

288
00:19:05,067 --> 00:19:07,000
She might hear you.

289
00:19:07,133 --> 00:19:07,933
Who?

290
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:09,967
Emma.

291
00:19:12,400 --> 00:19:14,167
She's here. She can hear us.

292
00:19:15,367 --> 00:19:16,933
She's behind these walls.

293
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:19,400
I can feel her.

294
00:19:20,433 --> 00:19:21,667
Jade, can you stop this
nonsense?

295
00:19:21,800 --> 00:19:23,100
Go get some rest.

296
00:19:23,233 --> 00:19:23,733
No!

297
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:27,600
I can't be at peace

298
00:19:30,600 --> 00:19:32,767
until I get Emma.

299
00:19:35,733 --> 00:19:36,833
What about your maid?

300
00:19:38,800 --> 00:19:40,167
She's useless.

301
00:19:41,533 --> 00:19:43,833
She doesn't want to say
what she knows.

302
00:19:45,133 --> 00:19:47,333
Let's get someone to keep
an eye on her.

303
00:19:47,467 --> 00:19:49,733
Flor might be hiding Emma
in her house.

304
00:19:49,867 --> 00:19:51,833
Teban went there.

305
00:19:52,900 --> 00:19:54,333
Emma wasn't there.

306
00:19:57,500 --> 00:19:58,533
But...

307
00:20:01,433 --> 00:20:03,767
I thought of a way

308
00:20:06,700 --> 00:20:09,133
to make her come out.

309
00:20:22,433 --> 00:20:24,000
Boss Logan told me to call some
people

310
00:20:24,133 --> 00:20:28,600
who will take Jade's video
once you haunt her in public.

311
00:20:28,733 --> 00:20:30,733
So that there will be different
angles.

312
00:20:30,867 --> 00:20:32,167
Where do you want to do this,
Emma?

313
00:20:32,300 --> 00:20:33,900
Somewhere crowded.

314
00:20:34,033 --> 00:20:36,500
I want many people
to see her insanity.

315
00:20:40,867 --> 00:20:42,833
Oh my God!

316
00:20:42,967 --> 00:20:45,433
My day is going well,
and then I saw this.

317
00:20:45,567 --> 00:20:47,567
Bro, there's a dead body!

318
00:20:48,767 --> 00:20:49,633
Looks like he was killed!

319
00:20:49,767 --> 00:20:51,100
Call the police!

320
00:20:51,233 --> 00:20:52,600
Where did you get that, boss?

321
00:20:56,933 --> 00:20:58,933
It came from my connections.

322
00:20:59,067 --> 00:21:00,833
Sgt. Ferrer sent it to me.

323
00:21:02,567 --> 00:21:04,200
Did someone kill him?

324
00:21:05,367 --> 00:21:07,400
Maybe he wronged a lot
of people.

325
00:21:08,500 --> 00:21:11,733
It's not easy to trace who did
that.

326
00:21:11,867 --> 00:21:13,633
And here's something worse.

327
00:21:13,767 --> 00:21:16,100
See where the dead body
was recovered.

328
00:21:17,467 --> 00:21:18,667
Darn it!

329
00:21:18,800 --> 00:21:20,800
That's Emma's fake grave.

330
00:21:23,267 --> 00:21:25,300
Jade found out
I'm still alive?

331
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:31,167
Jade probably had Altair killed.

332
00:21:43,133 --> 00:21:44,367
Hello, Emma.

333
00:21:44,500 --> 00:21:47,700
Flor, get out of there now.

334
00:21:47,833 --> 00:21:49,633
What? Why?

335
00:21:49,767 --> 00:21:51,700
Jade already knows I'm alive.

336
00:21:51,833 --> 00:21:55,733
She killed her private
investigator who helped us.

337
00:21:55,867 --> 00:21:56,833
What?

338
00:21:56,967 --> 00:21:58,100
Hurry.

339
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:00,833
Don't make it obvious.

340
00:22:00,967 --> 00:22:02,367
She might do something bad
to you.

341
00:22:10,533 --> 00:22:12,833
My God!

342
00:22:12,967 --> 00:22:13,767
<i> Flor?</i>

343
00:22:16,067 --> 00:22:16,967
<i> Flor!</i>

344
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:26,867
Love, do you need anything?

345
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:29,600
I'll ask Flor to make me some
coffee.

346
00:22:33,433 --> 00:22:34,600
Wait. Why...

347
00:22:34,733 --> 00:22:36,533
Why does your eyes seem
different?

348
00:22:36,667 --> 00:22:39,700
Are you okay? You look sick.

349
00:22:39,833 --> 00:22:42,133
Yes, love. I'm okay.

350
00:22:42,267 --> 00:22:45,933
I'm just a bit tired and busy
with the company's problem.

351
00:22:46,067 --> 00:22:49,433
That's why I don't get enough
sleep and can't relax.

352
00:22:49,600 --> 00:22:51,567
But I'm okay.

353
00:22:51,700 --> 00:22:54,500
Anyway, do you want coffee?

354
00:22:54,633 --> 00:22:55,933
Let me ask Flor.

355
00:23:03,133 --> 00:23:04,800
<i> Oh no!</i>

356
00:23:04,933 --> 00:23:06,900
<i> She escaped you!</i>

357
00:23:07,033 --> 00:23:08,367
<i> Too bad!</i>

358
00:23:09,733 --> 00:23:10,833
No.

359
00:23:10,967 --> 00:23:12,633
That can't be.

360
00:23:12,767 --> 00:23:16,000
Where did she go?
She was just here earlier.

361
00:23:16,133 --> 00:23:18,533
Who will make the coffee?

362
00:23:18,667 --> 00:23:20,733
Jade, I'll do it.

363
00:23:20,867 --> 00:23:23,167
I'll make the coffee.

364
00:23:23,333 --> 00:23:24,367
Calm down, okay?

365
00:23:24,500 --> 00:23:25,867
Okay.

366
00:23:27,133 --> 00:23:28,667
- Are you sure, love?
- Yes.

367
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:34,433
By the way,
did Mookie call you?

368
00:23:34,567 --> 00:23:36,733
She told me she was going out.

369
00:23:38,367 --> 00:23:39,833
She said she'd meet someone.

370
00:23:39,967 --> 00:23:40,933
She'll meet someone?

371
00:23:42,067 --> 00:23:42,967
Who?

372
00:23:43,100 --> 00:23:45,300
Who will Mookie meet? Tell me.

373
00:23:46,833 --> 00:23:49,100
She didn't tell me.

374
00:23:49,233 --> 00:23:52,000
<i> It's Emma. It has to be her.</i>

375
00:23:52,133 --> 00:23:54,033
<i>She's taking everyone
one by one.</i>

376
00:23:54,167 --> 00:23:55,900
<i> First, it was Ligaya.</i>

377
00:23:56,067 --> 00:23:58,067
<i> And now, Mookie?</i>

378
00:23:58,200 --> 00:23:59,333
No.

379
00:23:59,467 --> 00:24:00,133
No.

380
00:24:01,400 --> 00:24:02,800
No way in hell.

381
00:24:10,567 --> 00:24:14,233
I am so sorry
about what happened last time.

382
00:24:14,367 --> 00:24:16,567
Zayn scolded me.

383
00:24:16,700 --> 00:24:17,600
Mom.

384
00:24:17,733 --> 00:24:19,267
Zayn's Mom?

385
00:24:20,633 --> 00:24:22,167
Are they in a relationship?

386
00:24:22,300 --> 00:24:26,733
I want to court you again.

387
00:24:26,867 --> 00:24:28,400
Ador, no.

388
00:24:28,567 --> 00:24:33,967
What do you want me
to do to trust me again?

389
00:24:34,100 --> 00:24:35,467
I've changed.

390
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:37,067
I don't believe you!

391
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:42,367
I knew it.

392
00:24:42,500 --> 00:24:43,633
Emma's here.

393
00:24:43,767 --> 00:24:44,533
Move!

394
00:24:45,267 --> 00:24:47,533
You can't take my daughter
away from me!

395
00:24:47,667 --> 00:24:48,067
Auntie Jade!

396
00:24:48,233 --> 00:24:49,333
Darn you, Emma!

397
00:24:49,467 --> 00:24:51,833
You can't take Mookie from me!
